<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsum of head with indistinct minute punctures, remaining parts smooth with strong luster (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13B, D</figureCitation>
). Anterior incision of clypeus small and roundish, labrum small, roundish at apex; malar space about 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of middle ocellus; postocellar area weakly elevated, 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long; lateral furrows distinct, slightly divergent backwards, anterior part of middle groove distinct; POL: OOL: OCL = 3: 4: 6; head behind eyes weakly enlarged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13B, D</figureCitation>
). Antenna length about 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head breadth, club 1.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as antennomere 3, club breadth about 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
apical breadth of antennomere 3, antennomere 3 as long as longest axis of eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesonotum including mesoscutellum densely punctured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13E</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron indistinctly and finely punctured, hardly microsculptured, shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13H</figureCitation>
); mesosternum shallowly and weakly punctured. Median mesoscutal groove and notaulus broad and shallow; mesoscutellum roundly elevated without middle furrow; mesepisternum with a distinct oblique carina; cenchri narrow, distance between inner margin of cenchri 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longest axis of a cenchrus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal terga finely and densely microsculptured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13F</figureCitation>
). Tergum 1 with lateral carina distinct, posterior corner not produced, posterior margin broadly and roundly incised (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13F</figureCitation>
); middle process of sternum 7 broad, basal breadth about 1/3 breadth of sternite 7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13G</figureCitation>
); apical margin of ovipositor sheath truncate in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13K</figureCitation>
). Lancet with 51 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13L</figureCitation>
), middle serrulae distinctly narrowed toward truncate apex with 4-6 proximal subbasal teeth and 3-5 distal subbasal teeth, distance between serrulae about 2.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of serrula (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Asicimbex shengi Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in dorsal view C antenna D head in front view E thoracic notum F abdominal terga G leg H mesopleuron and metapleuron I lateral side of abdomen J lance K ovipositor sheath in lateral view L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707236" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">13M</figureCitation>
); lance long and slender, subapical annuli broadened, total length of annuli 5.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
